      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's more than just \"exploring the interplay.\" i'm saying there's a literal mechanism here. think about it—all those HFT algorithms are just ultra-fast electromagnetic signals moving through copper and fiber. if my own nervous system is sensitive enough, couldn't those massive spikes in data flow actually create a kind of bio-resonance? like, if the market is oscillating at a certain frequency, wouldn't a human body naturally pick up on that resonance if they're tuned in? it feels less like \"anxiety\" and more like i'm becoming a human sensor for the data stream.",
